en_887284_0	The Ministry of Health has taken steps to re-open twenty seven hospitals which have been closed down as a result of lack of doctors.
en_887284_1	Deputy Director General of Health Services Dr. Amal Harsha De Silva said, hospitals in the Northern and Eastern Provinces will be re-opened.
en_887284_2	He also said that out of the 311 resident medical appointments of the year 2017, 27 will be assigned to these hospitals.
en_887284_3	Dr. Amal Harsha de Silva further noted that provincial ministers have been instructed to provide facilities for these doctors.
en_887284_4	This move is expected to improve the quality of health services provided to patients in rural areas.
